Singer Portable has added another automobile to his garage. Portable recently got delivery of a Lexus E350 sedan car valued at N3 million. The singer took to his Instagram account to announce his newest acquisition.   I would’ve been a petroleum engineer, says Romeo     Olubukola Bolarinde plans 106 Expressions for June     Nigerian Idol 7 finale: Progress to go head-to-head with…   In his style, Portable sang his praises while thanking God for the new addition but not without a warning to all motorists to steer clear of his vehicle. He wrote: “Abeg no go spoil my motor, Zazuu Motor CEO, Dr. Zeh Nation.” The young singer, who became popular for his monster hit song, Zazuu Zeh, recently returned from his first trip to England, where he performed at some shows before visiting Dubai, UAE, where he met with his benefactor, Olamide, and later Istanbul, Turkey.